    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Germans use two past tenses:",
          "",
          "PERFECT TENSE (spoken):",
          "Ich habe gegessen. (I ate / I have eaten)",
          "",
          "PAST TENSE / PRÄTERITUM (written & formal):",
          "Ich aß. (I ate)",
          "Damals war alles anders. (Back then was different)",
          "",
          "WHEN TO USE PRÄTERITUM:",
          "Writing stories, reports, formal texts",
          "Telling longer narratives",
          "With sein, haben, and modal verbs (always)",
          "",
          "REGULAR VERBS:",
          "Add -TE to the stem",
          "machen → ich machte (I made)",
          "sagen → ich sagte (I said)",
          "arbeiten → ich arbeitete (I worked)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 49"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "ESSENTIAL IRREGULAR VERBS:",
          "",
          "SEIN (to be):",
          "ich war, du warst, er war, wir waren",
          "",
          "HABEN (to have):",
          "ich hatte, du hattest, er hatte, wir hatten",
          "",
          "WERDEN (to become):",
          "ich wurde, du wurdest, er wurde, wir wurden",
          "",
          "COMMON MODAL VERBS:",
          "können → ich konnte (I could)",
          "müssen → ich musste (I had to)",
          "wollen → ich wollte (I wanted to)",
          "",
          "Es war ein schöner Tag. (It was a nice day)",
          "Ich hatte keine Zeit. (I had no time)"
        ]
