    "lesson_id": "052",
    "trigger_word": "damit",
    "trigger_card_number": 857,
    "title": "LESSON 52: DA- & WO- COMPOUNDS",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 3,
        "content": [
          "Da- and wo- compounds replace prepositions",
          "with pronouns, referring back to things already",
          "mentioned in conversation.",
          "",
          "ENGLISH:",
          "I have a BALL. I play WITH IT sometimes.",
          "You play WITH WHAT? My BALL.",
          "",
          "GERMAN:",
          "Ich habe einen BALL. Ich spiele DAMIT.",
          "WOMIT spielst du? Meinen BALL.",
          "",
          "damit = da + mit (with it)",
          "womit = wo + mit (with what)",
          "",
          "For prepositions that begin with a vowel,",
          "'r' is inserted: woran, darauf, worauf, daran"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 52"
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 3,
        "content": [
          "DA-COMPOUNDS refer to things:",
          "",
          "damit (with it)",
          "dafür (for it)",
          "darauf (on it, for it)",
          "daran (on it, about it)",
          "davon (from it, about it)",
          "dabei (at it, with it)",
          "",
          "EXAMPLES:",
          "Ich warte auf den Bus. Ich warte darauf.",
          "(I'm waiting for the bus. I'm waiting for it)",
          "",
          "Ich denke an die Prüfung. Ich denke daran.",
          "(I think about the exam. I'm thinking about it)"
        ]
      },
      {
        "page": 3,
        "total_pages": 3,
        "content": [
          "WO-COMPOUNDS ask questions about things:",
          "",
          "womit? (with what?)",
          "wofür? (for what?)",
          "worauf? (on what? for what?)",
          "woran? (on what? about what?)",
          "wovon? (from what? about what?)",
          "",
          "Worauf wartest du? (What are you waiting for?)",
          "Woran denkst du? (What are you thinking about?)",
          "",
          "FOR PEOPLE, use preposition + wen/wem:",
          "Auf wen wartest du?",
          "(Who are you waiting for?)",
          "An wen denkst du?",
          "(Who are you thinking about?)"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
